Meaning of each value
0 â†’ minute 0 (exactly at the start of the hour)
23 â†’ hour 23 (11:00 PM)
* â†’ every day of the month
* â†’ every month
* â†’ every day of the week
ðŸ‘‰ So this runs every day at 11:00 PM

Command Part (Right Side)
/bin/bash /opt/scripts/daily_error_report.sh

Explanation

/bin/bash â†’ explicitly uses the Bash shell

/opt/scripts/daily_error_report.sh â†’ full path to your script

Why full paths are important in cron

Cron runs with a minimal environment

Relative paths may fail

Explicit shell + absolute paths = production best practice

What Happens at 11:00 PM Daily

Cron wakes up

Bash is invoked

daily_error_report.sh runs

Log analysis is performed

A new date-based error report is generated

How to verify it is working
Check cron logs
grep CRON /var/log/syslog      # Ubuntu/Debian
grep CRON /var/log/cron       # RHEL/CentOS

Test manually
/bin/bash /opt/scripts/daily_error_report.sh

Common production mistakes (avoid these)
Mistake	Result
Using sh instead of bash	Script may fail
Using relative paths	Cron cannot find files
Missing execute permission	Script wonâ€™t run
Fix permission
chmod +x /opt/scripts/daily_error_report.sh
